Burma Claims It Has No SARS - 2003-04-30
Burma's military government says the country has not recorded a case of Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome.  Burmese Deputy Health Minister Mya Oo says Rangoon has taken steps to prevent any SARS outbreak, including screening passengers with symptoms of the disease at Burmese airports.  Meanwhile, Burmese media report a man with SARS symptoms who died in a Burmese hospital last week did not have the virus. Doctors say the man died from heart disease and hypertension.
